Client Applications:

Users interact with the chat service through web or mobile clients.
Utilize WebSockets for real-time communication.
Chat Server:

Handles incoming and outgoing messages.
Publishes messages to Kafka and consumes messages for delivery.
Apache Kafka Cluster:

Serves as a distributed messaging system.
Ensures reliable and scalable message brokering.
Redis:

Manages user presence (online/offline status).
Caches frequently accessed data for quick retrieval.
Kafka Consumers:

Dedicated services that consume messages from Kafka topics.
Responsible for delivering messages to intended recipients.
  
